    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1959-03-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1959-03-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="276"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d276">
                <head>276. Memorandum From Director of Central Intelligence <persName
                        corresp="#p_DJF1" type="from">Dulles</persName> to the President’s Special
                    Assistant for National Security Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_GG1" type="to"
                        >Gray</persName>)<note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d276fn0">Source:
                        Eisenhower Library, Whitman File, Intelligence Matters (9). Secret. The
                        source text bears no drafting information.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1959-03-31">March 31, 1959</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>[<hi rend="italic">less than 1 line of source text not declassified</hi>]
                        Resistance Program</item>
                </list>
                <p>1. Referring to your recent conversation on 30 March concerning my proposal by
                    memorandum of 27 March 1959 on the above subject,<note n="1" xml:id="d276fn1"
                        >See <ref target="#d277">Document 277</ref> and its attachment.</note> I <pb
                        facs="0587" n="555" xml:id="pg_555"/> wish to assure you that full
                    consideration has been given to the points that you have raised.</p>
                <p>[<hi rend="italic">3 paragraphs (21 lines of source text) not
                    declassified</hi>]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">
                            <persName corresp="#p_DAW1">Allen W. Dulles</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
